<event name="SALT_QUEST_2_SUCCESS_NORMAL">
	<text>You've finally made your way to the prison hold, labeled "Exotic Creature Containment." You shoot a couple guards on the way, picking up a keycard from one of them, which you use to unlock the Salt Man's cell, where you find a massive gray creature leaning against a wall as if waiting for you. "I'm going to take a shot in the dark and say you aren't with the Guild, considering that green ooze all over your chest seems like it belongs to someone else." He sticks out his massive hand. "Name's Obyn, though most just call me 'Salt Man'. Take the view in while you can, I'm not a sight you see often."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>You'd be right, Sylvan sent us to find you.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"I- did I hear you correctly? Sylvan, as in THE Sylvan? The traveling merchant? That's the one?" The Salt Man seems to have an air of both excitement and reservation.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Yeah, that one. With the big spooky ship who says stranger a lot.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"My dearest is here? Oh heavens, I am hardly prepared for such a reunion... I- wait, well where is he?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Oh... well he's not actually here.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Of course not. I mean, figures. What's several years fighting side by side, friends and more, hiding amongst a bunch of lizards and seeing the galaxy? All's well until you want to embark on a quest to find the rest of your species, and suddenly it's time for a break up. That little slimeball's too much of a coward to leave behind his comfy little life selling weapons to murder hobos, so of course he can't even show his face to me for the last 6 years!"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Calm down, we have to get you out of here first.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Right, right. Fine. Did you happen to meet my crew? Considering my cowardly ex couldn't be bothered to find me, I doubt he knew I was here, so you must have got my coords from somewhere." You inform Obyn you have in fact met his crew. "Great. At least I can count on them not to leave me behind. Alright, let's get out of here quick. You broke your way in quite fine, but I doubt the Guild's going to let us waltz out either."</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event>
											<text>Obyn follows you through the corridors of the facility, where you make your way back to the hangar where your ship is held. You hurry inside and take off from the massive facility and make your way back down to the market. You begin to think you might actually make it out of here without a fight, when a Clansman cruiser jumps in out of nowhere! "Ah, there you are you little fecal droppingsss! Ssstealing from the Guild only endssss you up in one ssspot! A shallow grave!"</text>
											<triggeredEvent event="TEMP_OBYN_JUMP" jumps="1"/>
											<crewMember amount="1" class="unique_obyn_temp">Obyn</crewMember>
											<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_CRUISER" hostile="true"/>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
