<event name="SYLVAN_DOES_AN_EX_MACHINA">
	<text>As more ships approach, underneath the shadow of the massive dissection center, it becomes apparent this is the end. "The EHG hasss had enough of you messsing around in our sssector! You Renegades hold no regard for the sssanctity of the Kleptocracccy's control over thessse nebulas or our right to exploit the resssourccces within them! Ssssurrender the Sssalt Man or be annihilated!"</text>
	<variable name="ach_boss_clancruiser" op="set" val="1"/>
	<clearTriggeredEvent name="TEMP_OBYN_JUMP"/>
	<choice hidden="true" req="pilot" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>No, screw you! I'm tired of listening to your dumb accents!</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Oi! Mate, you don't have to be rude! Anywaysss, you've made your choiccce. Time to sssuffer the consssequencc-" The Clansman doesn't get a chance to finish his sentence when a salvo of lasers takes out his shields then engines, causing him to spiral into a nearby ship and crash into the market below in a fiery ball of destruction! From the sky descends Sylvan's ship, followed by the Salt Man's own cruiser, firing away into the fleet. "Crap crap crap it'sssss HIM! RUN!" The Clansmen scatter. You knew Sylvan had a particularly... well armed ship, but you didn't think he was strong enough to scare away an entire fleet. Evidently, his departure from the Guild left quite the impression.</text>
			<choice hidden="true" req="unique_obyn_temp" blue="false" lvl="1">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>You watch as Sylvan and the Salt cruiser land in front of you. "I hope I'm not too late sssstranger!" Sylvan laughs nervously, then faces Obyn, but before he can speak he's cut off. "If you dare address me as 'stranger', I'll crack open your skull." "Heheh, I wouldn't dream of it Obyn. It'ssss been a long time. How'ssss life?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Oh you know, just wandering this scum infested sector and being held captive in labs where they mutilate people for the fun of it." Obyn pauses. "6. Years. And you ask me 'how's life?!'" Sylvan laughs nervously. "I think they call that taxidermy. I did alwayssss find it dissstasssteful..." Sylvan pauses. "I'm ssssorry Obyn, for leaving. I didn't think I could bear to sssee you again, after ssso much time, but when I heard you might be in trouble, I came. But I... I wassss sstill too much of a coward, ssso I sssent thessse friendssss of mine inssstead."</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Keep listening.</text>
								<event>
									<text>Obyn sighs. "It's hard to be mad at you. But you have a lot of making up to do. But in the end, you did come. And that's worth something, I guess. We can talk the rest out later. Now, come here." The two lean in for a hug, though Sylvan keeps enough distance away from their bodies to prevent his flesh from being singed from Obyn's salty exterior. This is quite the ironic relationship, you realize.</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_OBYN"/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Look guys, this is sweet and all, but could you save the personal stuff for later please?</text>
								<event>
									<text>The two glare at you for a moment, but then Sylvan chuckles. "Ah yesss, I got lossst in the moment again. You have my mossst sssincere thanksss ssstranger! What kind of man would I be if I didn't give you a reward for your efforts!"</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_OBYN"/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="unique_obyn_temp" blue="false" lvl="0" max_lvl="0">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="unique_obyn_temp" blue="false" max_group="1">
		<text>Give up the Salt Man.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Salt Man turns to you in shock, but you have little choice. You can't take on an entire fleet! You push him forward, where a team of Clansmen pick him up. "Wissse choiccce ssson. Looksss like you'll live to sssee tomorrow after all. But do usss a favor, and don't come back."</text>
			<removeCrew class="unique_obyn_temp">
				<clone>false</clone>
				<text>You literally got the Salt Man a few minutes ago and you've already given him up. Good going.</text>
			</removeCrew>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="GNOME_DOES_AN_EX_MACHINA">
	<text>As more ships approach, underneath the shadow of the massive dissection center, it becomes apparent this is the end. "The EHG hasss had enough of you messsing around in our sssector! You Renegades hold no regard for the sssanctity of the Kleptocracccy's control over thessse nebulas or our right to exploit the resssourccces within them! Ssssurrender the Sssalt Man or be annihilated!"</text>
	<variable name="ach_boss_clancruiser" op="set" val="1"/>
