<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW">
	<text>You watch as Sylvan and the Salt cruiser land in front of you. Sylvan understandably remains silent at the moment, but with the help of Obyn's former crew, carry over a large crate of scrap. They transfer over some blueprints for Obyn's vessel as well to you, figuring the Federation might have some use for them. You can tell Sylvan is distraught about losing Obyn, but it's too late now. "Sssstranger, I ssstill have an old gun of hisss on hand. I... I don't think I can keep it around any longer. Sssso, perhapsss it isss bessst if you take it. I don't blame you for thisss, but... oh well. What ussse isss having a ssship like mine when I can't even sssave my friendsss, huh? Hmph."</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_SALT</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
	<weapon name="SALT_LAUNCHER"/>
</event>
<event name="CHAOS_SALT_REWARD_NOCREW">
	<text>Unfortunately, Obyn didn't survive the fight. Terrified the gnome may actually eat your liver, you look back at it but can't seem to find it anywhere. Worried you may have lost it, you look around for a while but slowly start to forget what you were looking for. Eventually you come to a stop and realize you have no idea what you're doing. Confused why you're here at all, you head back to the bridge and prepare to leave.</text>
	<variable name="chaos_mode" op="set" val="0"/>
	<removeCrew class="gnome">
		<clone>false</clone>
		<text></text>
	</removeCrew>
</event>
<event name="SYLVAN_SALT_REWARD_OBYN">
	<text>Sylvan, with the help of Obyn and his crew, carry over a large crate of scrap. Obyn transfers over some blueprints for his vessel as well to you, figuring the Federation might have some use for them. Sylvan heads back to his ship, but Obyn stands between the three ships with a look of indecision on his face. Sylvan turns to look at him but Obyn shakes his head. "I can't go with you, old friend. We just... well you know how it went. I can forgive, but I can't forget. You're a merchant, and I'm a bounty hunter. In this climate, I guess they're sort of the same thing, but there's a difference somewhere. And I still haven't given up on my quest. There's more of my people out there, I'm sure of it. I still remember the day I fled my colony... well, I have to keep looking. I can't just give up."</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_SALT</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>You could come with us, be a hero, then continue your quest after.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"A hero of the Federation? You know how to win me over... I've tried being a bounty hunter, but things obviously didn't work well, and the life of a merchant isn't for me. I'm sure we'll see each other again Sylvan. As for you, Pepper." Obyn turns to face the Rockman you spoke with earlier. "I'm trusting you with my ship. Take good care of it." Obyn turns to you. "Now, shall we go? I see adventure on the horizon! Who knows, maybe on the way I'll find a clue. Only way to go is to stay hopeful." With that, he salutes to Sylvan and the two depart.</text>
			<transformRace class="unique_obyn_temp">unique_obyn</transformRace>
			<variable name="ach_crew_obyn" op="set" val="1"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Entice him to go with his old crew and continue his quest.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Yes, I suppose there's no time to waste. Goodbye, Sylvan. I'm certain we'll reunite again. And as for you, Renegade. You have my gratitude. And since I know gratitude is all but an accepted currency in these parts, maybe this weapon will satisfy you as well. Till next time." With that, he salutes to Sylvan and the two depart, flying away in their ships.</text>
			<weapon name="SALT_LAUNCHER"/>
			<removeCrew class="unique_obyn_temp">
				<clone>false</clone>
				<text></text>
			</removeCrew>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="CHAOS_SALT_REWARD_OBYN">
	<text>Obyn looks on in shock at what just happened. For once, he finally looks down and seems to be aware of the gnome's presence. "In all my years exploring the galaxy looking for more of my kind I have seen many, many strange things. But never once have I ever seen something like this. What ARE you? Gods? Is this gnome a god?" Obyn wavers, wobbling slightly in the legs.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>I have no idea what's happening either, but the gnome wants you to come with us.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"If the gnome wants me to come, then I guess I'm coming. God help us all. I guess I have no need for my ship anymore, so you can have it. Maybe it'll appease the gnome, who knows."</text>
			<playSound>gnome_keepliver</playSound>
			<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_SALT</unlockCustomShip>
			<transformRace class="unique_obyn_temp">unique_obyn</transformRace>
