	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the Clansman.</text>
		<event>
			<text>For all you know, this could be a trap. You ignore the Clansman.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="CLAN_SPICES" unique="true">
	<text>Though the Guild normally stays to nebulas like the Slugs, it appears a trading outpost has been set up in this clearing to attract better business. That appears to have worked well... because a jet black and very powerful Slug ship is holding the lodge hostage and demanding the Clansmen hand over their 'exotic spices.' Probably drugs, if you had to guess.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack the black Slug ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You arm the weapons and attack the strange Slug ship.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_SPICES_KNIGHT" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Help the black Slug ship out and take the drugs yourself.</text>
		<event>
			<text>To do this you'll have to kill the Clansmen without destroying their station. Be careful!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_SPICES_CLAN" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The origin of this new Slug vessel will have to go unknown. It's too risky to get involved when there's more important things at hand.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

