<event name="NEBULA_CLAN_RODEO" unique="true">
	<text>As you explore the nearby system you find a large gathering of foreign ships, mostly belonging to the Guild. It looks friendly enough, so you land nearby and take closer look, and see what appears to be a rodeo!</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ask about the rodeo.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You're greeted by a Ranger with an oversized hat, who explains the basics. "We've rounded up quite a handful of Equinoidsss, and we're going to hold a grand sssspace rodeo! You can enter one of your crew if you want, for a sssmall entrance fee of 25 ssscrap. Whatever particccipant lastsss the longessst winsss the prize, a weapon we definitely didn't sssteal! It's one big-assss beam, if that enticccesss you!"</text>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="1" blue="false">
				<text>Enter the rodeo.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You hand over some scrap to the Clansman, who reassures you by saying "Don't worry about your crew either, we ain't rookiesss here! We've got a whole medical team on ssstandbye in cassse thingssss go sssouth!"</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-25" max="-25"/>
					</item_modify>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Send out a random crew member.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew steps up to the competitors' chamber amongst some other aliens. Some Clansmen finish up preparing, and then usher in the first few contestants...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Wish your crew luck and wait for the results.</text>
								<event load="CLAN_RODEO_NORMAL"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_SOLDIER">
						<text>(Soldier Crew) Your Soldier has some training in mounted combat. Send him.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew steps up to the competitors' chamber amongst some other aliens. Some Clansmen finish up preparing, and then usher in the first few contestants...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Wish your crew luck and wait for the results.</text>
								<event load="CLAN_RODEO_GOOD"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_JERRY">
						<text>(Jerry) Jerry really really wants to ride the horse! Send him.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Jerry steps up to the competitors' chamber amongst some other aliens. Some Clansmen finish up preparing, and then usher in the first few contestants...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Wish your crew luck and wait for the results.</text>
								<event load="CLAN_RODEO_JERRY"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_LIZARD">
						<text>(Lizard Crew) Your Lizard has ridden Equinoids before. Send him.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew steps up to the competitors' chamber amongst some other aliens. Some Clansmen finish up preparing, and then usher in the first few contestants...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Wish your crew luck and wait for the results.</text>
								<event load="CLAN_RODEO_GOOD"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
				<text>You don't have any eligible riders with you. And don't even think about putting the drones on the horse...</text>
				<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Inquire about these 'Equinoids' instead.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"No one really knowsss where they came from firssst, but through the medium of sssspace travel they've been introduccced to hundredsss of planetsss around the galaxy. They're pretty passsive asss long asss you're kind to them."</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Buy a tamed Equinoid.</text>
						<event>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
							</item_modify>
							<crewMember amount="1" class="pony_tamed"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Buy one of their younger, untamed Equinoids.</text>
						<event>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-20" max="-20"/>
							</item_modify>
							<crewMember amount="1" class="pony"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Interesting, but no reason to stick around.</text>
						<event/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Our mission is too important to waste time entering a contest.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Apparently, you aren't interested in the prospect of riding alien horses. You're pretty boring, all in all.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="CLAN_RODEO_NORMAL">
	<event>
		<text>Your crew mounts the equinoid and gives it their best, but the beast is too unruly and your crew is flung face first into the dirt. A painful failure, and a loss of scrap for your mission.</text>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Your crew mounts the equinoid, and clings on for dear life while they're flung around. Somehow, they manage to stay on, and by the end of the competition it turns out they're the winner! The Slugs bring out the prize.</text>
		<weapon name="GIFTLIST_BIG_BEAM"/>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="CLAN_RODEO_GOOD">
	<event>
		<text>Your crew mounts the Equinoid and gives it their best, but the beast is too unruly and your crew is flung face first into the dirt. A painful failure, and a loss of scrap for your mission.</text>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Your crew mounts the Equinoid, and clings on for dear life while they're flung around. Somehow, they manage to stay on, and by the end of the competition it turns out they're the winner! The Slugs bring out the prize.</text>
