		<weapon name="GIFTLIST_BIG_BEAM"/>
	</event>
</eventList>
<event name="CLAN_RODEO_JERRY">
	<text>As soon as Jerry mounts the wild beast, the Equinoid is immediately calmed, standing passively while Jerry gently strokes its mane. There's an outroar from the crowd calling you a cheater, but after a quick drug test to verify you didn't subdue the horse you're declared the winner and the prize is brought out!</text>
	<achievement>ACH_JERRY_RODEO</achievement>
	<weapon name="GIFTLIST_BIG_BEAM"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>As you prepare to leave the rodeo, you see an Equinoid running towards you dragging the Ranger by its lead. "Woah, woah! Ssstop!" The Clansmen brings the Equinoid to a halt, but only because the horse has stopped right before Jerry. "Thisss one broke out of containment and chasssed you all the way out here. Guesss ssshe really likesss your friend. Might asss well keep her, we got plenty more."</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" combat="2" class="pony_tamed"/>
			<!--<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_PONY</unlockCustomShip>-->
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_CLAN_PHEROMONES" unique="true">
	<preventQuest/>
	<text>You've seen a lot of things in your travels, but you don't think you've ever seen the wastes of half a Mantis fleet lying before a Guild megastructure. A massive mechanic arm appears to be collecting the wrecks one by one and moving them towards a small docking bay.</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Investigate further.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You pilot towards the structure and enter through a hangar door, where you're greeted by a Clansman. "Oh god, you aren't here to ssshut usss down, are you?"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>I don't think so.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh thank god. Wait, ssso why are you here? Have you come to watch my operation? Thisss here isss a pheromone extraction plant. The pheromone bussinesss isss booming, and we want to get a firm grip on it before thossse Free Mantiss bastardsss monopolizzze the whole thing."</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Buy some pheromones.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Pleasssure doing bussinessss with you! Jusssst don't tell the Federation. Or the Hive. Actually, jusssst don't tell anyone pleassse."</text>
							<augment name="CREW_STIMS"/>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-15" max="-15"/>
							</item_modify>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Where did all the Mantis come from?</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Oh well uh... we bought them from the Ghosssstsss. Yeah, that sssoundsss... believable."</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Then where did the Ghosts get this many Mantis ships from?</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Thhhheeeee... Mantissss ssstore?"</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>I didn't know that was a thing.</text>
										<event>
											<text>"Oh no yeah, it'sss definitely real! I can give you the coordinatesss, if you'd like!"</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>You're lying.</text>
												<event>
													<text>"Oh pissss off Federation! You can't judge me!" The Clansman scurries away and sounds the alarm. Looks like we have to fight!</text>
													<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_PHEROMONES" hostile="true"/> 
													<choice hidden="true">
														<text>Continue...</text>
														<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
													</choice>
												</event>
											</choice>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Sure!</text>
												<event>
													<text>"Uhhhh, ok..." The Clansman quickly draws out a pen and scribbles down some barely legible numbers, hands them to you, then scurries off.</text>
													<quest event="NEBULA_QUEST_CLAN_PHEROMONES_STORE"/>
												</event>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Sounds cool, but we don't have any reason to stick around.</text>
						<event/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Best not to get involved.</text>
		<event>
			<text>If you don't want to risk ending up like these Mantis, you probably shouldn't get any closer.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="CLAN_PHEROMONES_DEMAND">
	<text>"Alright, you've killed my men, now what? Are you going to ssshut down my facccility? Arressst me? Make me do an embarrassssing danccce?"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Shut down his facility.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You don't technically have the authority to do this, but that's never stopped you before. You pretend you know what you're doing and seize all that you can carry, then order them to close down the building. You know they probably won't, but in the end you got what you wanted.</text>
			<augment name="CREW_STIMS"/>
			<autoReward level="MED">fuel_only</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Arrest him.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You don't actually have handcuffs on you, and you aren't really sure what you're doing. Fortunately the Clansman doesn't seem to know Federation law very well either, so when you tell him it's standard for Federation criminals to do service aboard the ship holding the arrest, he doesn't question it.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_clansman"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Make him dance.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Sorrowfully, the Clansman does a waltz, but eventually breaks down into a sobbing heap. You take pity on the poor creature and only steal some of his scrap instead of all of it.</text>
			<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_ZOLTAN">
		<text>(Zoltan Crew) Carry out this arrest in an official manner.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Your Zoltan breaks out a pair of handcuffs from somewhere and cuffs the Clansmen one by one. They order the facility shut down, citing various codes if you hadn't known better would have assumed were made up, then ushers the Clansmen aboard your ship and confiscated several crates of supplies. When you ask what happens next, your Zoltan shrugs and figures you might as well make use of all this.</text>
			<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_clansman"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="NEBULA_QUEST_CLAN_PHEROMONES_STORE">
	<text>Even though it's more than likely that Clansman was lying, you still take a trip to the coordinates he specified. Fascinatingly, you see a junkyard of Mantis ships with a Ghost-populated Mantis ship guarding it.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_PHEROMONES_MANTISSTORE" hostile="false"/>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Excuse me, is this the Mantis store?</text>
		<event>
			<text>It takes a few silent moments until your translator can work out the quirks of Ghost dialect - "Yes, and welcome. We sell used Mantis ships. Our stock is greatly diminished after a large shipment was ordered by the members of a renowned Guild, but there's surely a pleasant model still available for your needs."</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Buy a Mantis ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>This is probably the most scrap you've ever spent on one item before, but hopefully it's worth it. The Ghosts bring over a Mantis ship, which you find still contains the corpses of the previous crew, and their weapons as well!</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-500" max="-500"/>
					</item_modify>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>While you don't have much use for the ship itself, you might as well scrap all that you can. You start with the weapons...</text>
							<weapon name="LIST_WEAPONS_ALL_CRAPBUCKET"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>You pull another weapon off of the hull.</text>
									<weapon name="LIST_WEAPONS_ALL_CRAPBUCKET"/>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event>
											<text>You pull another weapon off of the hull.</text>
											<weapon name="LIST_WEAPONS_ALL_CRAPBUCKET"/>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event>
													<text>You pull another weapon off of the hull.</text>
													<weapon name="LIST_WEAPONS_ALL_CRAPBUCKET"/>
													<choice hidden="true">
														<text>Continue...</text>
														<event>
															<text>You pull another weapon off of the hull.</text>
															<weapon name="LIST_WEAPONS_ALL_CRAPBUCKET"/>
															<choice hidden="true">
																<text>Continue...</text>
																<event load="BOUGHT_THE_GHOST_SHIP"/>
															</choice>
														</event>
													</choice>
												</event>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Fight the Ghosts!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You arm the weapons and attack the Ghost ship.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Well, there's not much reason to stick around.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>I've seen enough.</text>
		<event>
			<text>This is too much, even for you. Some things just aren't meant to be known, seen, or interacted with. This is one of those you reckon, and steer course as far away as possible.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="NEBULA_QUEST_CLAN_PHEROMONES_STORE_CHOICE">
	<text>The Ghosts are gone, but the shipyard still appears to have many Ghosts wandering about. Do you risk salvaging some supplies before you go?</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Loot some stuff.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You scrounge around in the Mantis ships and grab some more supplies, but an angry team of Ghosts climbs aboard to avenge their fallen friends!</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
			<boarders min="2" max="3" class="phantom_goul"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Don't take the risk and leave.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="BOUGHT_THE_GHOST_SHIP">
	<text>Though you've taken everything you need from the ship for now, you figure there's no harm in sending the wreck back to the Federation hangar... because why not?</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_STUPIDGHOST</unlockCustomShip>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_CLAN_PLUSHIES" unique="true">
	<text>It seems you've found another lodge established within the nebula. Oddly enough, it seems to have been repurposed as a... tourist location?</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_CLAN_LODGE" hostile="false"/>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Board and check it out.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A Clansman Ranger is leaning against a wall, talking to a small gathering of Zoltan officials, who leave shortly after you enter. "Pffft, imagine being sssuch a ssstick in the mud. Those Zoltan came here to assssk if I have a PERMIT to run thissss ssstore! Whossse sssector do they think thissss isss anywaysss? Didn't even buy anything..."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
