	</event>
	<event>
		<text>"I- are these Slug narcotics?" A Rock Crusader looks down at the drugs, but they're quickly scoop up by a Saboteur on the ship. "Yessss, we'll take them!"</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
		<remove name="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="KNIGHT_COALITION_SUZERAIN">
	<event>
		<text>The Suzerain beams aboard, but only to immediately detonate a fire bomb that damages the ship! It was a trick!</text>
		<damage amount="3" system="random" effect="fire"/>
		<boarders min="1" max="1" class="mantis_suzerain"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>True to his word, the Suzerain beams aboard your ship, ready to turn on his old crew-mates.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" combat="1" class="mantis_suzerain"/>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_CHOICE" unique="true">
	<text>Short range scans show two Slug vessels are in a dogfight at this beacon, one belong to the Knights, and the other to the Clairvoyants.</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_LIGHTNEBULA"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Get involved.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You make your presence known, flying towards the ships. But who will you attack?</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>The Knights!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You arm the weapons and attack the Knight vessel.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_CHOICE_KNIGHT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="SLUG_NARCOTICS">
				<text>(Slug Narcotics) Bribe the Knights to stop fighting.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It appears the Knights are willing to swallow their pride and surrender if it means they get free hard drugs.</text>
					<remove name="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Clairvoyant ship thanks you and offers a weapon.</text>
							<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>The Clairvoyants!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You arm the weapons and attack the Clairvoyant vessel.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_CHOICE_CLAIRVOYANT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Don't get involved.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Slugs have never been known to be reliable allies, so you don't bother helping any side.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_PROTESTERS" unique="true">
	<text>You jump when a disembodied voice suddenly speaks to you. From behind, a Saboteur uncloaks, wearing a pin of the Knight logo. "You're... an outsssider, right? The one Sssslocknog sssent. Normally I'd kill you on the ssspot, but I think we can work together here. There'ssss sssome pesssky reformisssstss nearby who are trying to overhaul our government. We want them dead. Kill them, I pay you. Deal?"</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Accept.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Saboteur leads you to a small moon with a Slug colony where several Slugs are protesting, led by a rogue Clairvoyant vessel. Take out their leader, and the rest will likely shut up.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_CLAIRVOYANT_PROTESTER" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Attack!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You raise the weapons and engage the ship.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="SLUG_NARCOTICS">
				<text>(Slug Narcotics) Bribe the Clairvoyant to turn on its own people.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It seems drugs outweigh any moral quandaries in Slug society. The Clairvoyants take hold of the drugs, then turn their weapons upon the colonists, forcing them to surrender. Behind you, the Knight is so humored by your 'creative' problem solving he offers an even larger reward.</text>
					<remove name="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Refuse.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Saboteur frowns and beams away to whatever ship is hiding nearby in the nebula watching you.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_PROTESTERS_WIN" unique="true">
	<text>The rest of the colony is terrified. "Pleasssse, all we want isss peacce! The Kleptocraccccy isss sssso needlesssly cruel, regardlesss of the king! We want to progressss Sslug sssociety into sssomething the ressst of the galaxy can look at with more than dissstasste!"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them and force the colony to surrender.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You ignore the colonists, raising your weapons and firing a warning shot. This sends them running for cover, and inevitably surrendering. The Saboteur returns and thanks you for your help, and rewards you as promised.</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Kill the Saboteur and free the colony.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You draw your blaster, and quickly spin around to blast the Saboteur. They're faster at first, but quickly get lost in the unfamiliar corridors of your ship and are dispatched with relative ease. Though a future Knight vessel will likely return to prey on the colony, they're free for now, and reward you in a somewhat unconventional way.</text>
			<damage amount="-7"/>
			<upgrade amount="1" system="shields"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="BLUELIST_FIRE_ALL">
		<text>(Fire Weapon) Make an example, torch the colony.</text>
		<event>
			<text>In a short period of time, the colony is ablaze and about half of its population dead. It's a gruesome display that will undoubtedly be used as propaganda in the future, but it's had quite the impression on the Saboteur. So amazed at your dedication to the task, he even offers to join your crew!</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_saboteur"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_SHAKESPEARE" unique="true">
	<text>"Hail th're did Feed'ration. Though mine own w'rds might beest rough, I asketh thee to holdeth with me. I may give you nay harmeth, lest thee stow thine weapons 'r brandish dram m're than the bravado one might beest accustom'd to. Aye? Art these reasonable t'rms 'r might we beest needing a duel?"</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Slug captain looks at you expectantly, though you don't understand a word he said.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Try to speak back in whatever language that was.</text>
				<event load="KNIGHT_SHAKESPEARE_GUESS"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="unique_haynes">
				<text>(Haynes) Haynes recognizes the language.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Haynes explains that the Slugs are speaking in old Earth English. After a quick translation, you learn the Slugs are offering a truce, which you accept and bring back a weapon from their ship as a sign of goodwill!</text>
					<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_SLUG">
				<text>(Slug Crew) Have your Slug speak with them.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Your Slug bickers back and forth with the knights for a while, then reports back to you. "They sssspeak fine, they're jusssst ssstubborn and refussse to talk to ussss normally. They sssseem to want to make friendssss though, and are offering fuel."</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">fuel_only</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_ENGI">
				<text>(Engi Crew) Analyze their speech patterns to translate.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Language detected: old Earth English. Updating databases..." Your Engi explains the Slugs don't wish to fight, but actually wish to give you some fuel out of good will.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">fuel_only</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="KNIGHT_SHAKESPEARE_GUESS">
	<event>
		<text>You fumble out some meaningless garble in hopeless imitation of the Slug. They obviously don't fall for it, and attack you out of outrage for your pathetic attempt.</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="SLUG_NARCOTICS">
			<text>Bribe them with the narcotics.</text>
			<event load="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Though your attempt at replicating the Slug's speech is pathetic, they don't seem particularly offended. Laughing tremendously at you, they invite you on-board their ship, and surprisingly offer some repairs and supplies.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
		<damage amount="-7"/>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="NEBULA_KNIGHT_JAILER" unique="true">
	<text>A Knighted Jailer flies past, only to briefly sling an insult at you. "Pissss off Federation, don't get involved lesssst you want a bullet in your ssskull!"</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_KNIGHT_JAILER" hostile="false"/> 
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack the Jailer.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You power up your weapons and engage the Slug vessel.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/> 
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="FIREARMS_AND_TELEPORT">
		<text>(Armories + Teleporter) Storm the Jailer.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Your crew, armed to the teeth, board the Jailer and quickly take down the Slug crew staffing it. With the jailers turned prisoners, you free everyone locked up who you don't think will kill you immediately.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="LIST_CREW_FEDERATION"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="SLUG_NARCOTICS" hidden="true">
		<text>Bribe them with the narcotics to let the prisoners go.</text>
		<event load="KNIGHT_JAILER_BRIBE"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">	
		<text>Ignore the Jailer.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You aren't in the mood to hold a jailbreak today. You distance yourself from the Jailer.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="SURRENDER_KNIGHT_JAILER"> 
	<text>"Crap, you're better armed than predicted. Uh, will you let usss go if you take thissss prisssoner?"</text>
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Accept a prisoner.</text>
		<event>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug"/>
			<ship hostile="false"/> 
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Refuse and keep fighting.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_JAILER_DESTROY">
	<text>The Jailer has been destroyed. While an excess of scrap remains, it's very unlikely any prisoners survived.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_JAILER_KILL">
	<text>The crew of the Jailer has been emptied. You scrap the externals of the ship.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Check the prisoners.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It appears most of the prisoners are dissenters from Nights' reign. A Saboteur loyal to Slocknog, recognizing you as the Federation ship sent by his hero, offers to work for you.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_saboteur"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="KNIGHT_JAILER_BRIBE">
	<text>The Jailer seems more than willing to betray their nation in turn for some hard drugs.</text>
	<remove name="SLUG_NARCOTICS"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Check the prisoners.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It appears most of the prisoners are dissenters from Nights' reign. A Saboteur loyal to Slocknog, recognizing you as the Federation ship sent by his hero, offers to work for you.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="slug_saboteur"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

